text: Reinhard Wagner (November 16, 1876 - April 2, 1964) was an American gymnast. He competed in four events at the 1904 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1876 births Category:1964 deaths Category:American male artistic gymnasts Category:Olympic gymnasts of the United States Category:Gymnasts at the 1904 Summer Olympics Category:People from Cochem-Zell
